{
  "info": {
    "name": "PH Assignment 4 GearUp",
    "description": "GearUp - Sports & Outdoor Gear Rental REST API.\n\nHow to use:\n1. Set the `rootUrl` variable (default http://localhost:5001). `base` derives from it as {{rootUrl}}/api/v1.\n2. Run Auth > Login (Admin/Provider/Customer) - the token is auto-saved to {{adminToken}} / {{providerToken}} / {{customerToken}}.\n3. Fill the id variables (gearId, rentalOrderId, paymentId, userId, categoryId) from earlier responses as you go.\n\nAll responses follow { success, message, meta?, data }. Errors follow { success, message, errorDetails }.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register Customer",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base}}/auth/register",
              "host": [
                "{{base}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Alice Customer\",\n  \"email\": \"alice@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\n  \"role\": \"CUSTOMER\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "description": "Public. Roles allowed: CUSTOMER or PROVIDER only."
          },
          "response": []
        },
